   {:e #blake3 "060fee552c2cea49c2b11134ca57d2065a90eeff609a958b359fc9752db78fa4" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: frontier_recommendation() IS called unconditionally at observe.rs:813. It returned None in the dogfood because: (a) Explore needs :pkg/* entities — these are NEVER created by any braid command (dead in production, only works in tests), (b) Deepen needs concepts with member_count >= 3 and variance > 0.1 — innate concepts start at 0/0.0, (c) Bridge needs concept pairs with disjoint member sets — all concepts had jaccard=1.00 due to concept collapse. After CCE-FIX-1 (threshold raise to 0.50), many observations will be uncategorized. After harvest, emergent concepts will form with differentiated members. Then Deepen and Bridge will fire naturally. However, the generic fallback 'what connects X to Y?' from compute_steering_question (concept.rs:1358) is still the ONLY output when frontier_recommendation returns None. This template never adapts to content.\n\nTWO CHANGES:\n\n1. Add FrontierKind::Narrow as a DIAGNOSTIC safety net:\n   - fn narrow_candidates(store: &Store) -> Vec<FrontierRec>\n   - Fires when mean jaccard across concept pairs > 0.8 (concept collapse state)\n   - Produces: 'concepts are converging — try observing a specific file, function, or error message rather than a whole package'\n   - Score: 1.0 (always high priority when collapse detected)\n   - This catches the pathological state that the threshold fix should prevent, providing actionable guidance if it recurs.\n\n2. Replace the generic 'what connects X to Y?' fallback with the contextual observation hint:\n   - In compute_steering_question (concept.rs:1358), instead of finding the nearest OTHER concept and asking a generic question, use the observation's entity matches to suggest specific investigation targets.\n   - If entity_matches is non-empty: 'investigate how {matched_entity} interacts with other parts of the codebase'\n   - If concept is Joined with surprise > 0.3: 'this observation is at the boundary of {concept_name} — what makes it different from typical {concept_name} observations?'\n   - Only fall back to 'what connects X to Y?' if no entity matches and low surprise.\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) FrontierKind::Narrow variant exists with Display impl. (B) narrow_candidates fires when mean jaccard > 0.8. (C) compute_steering_question produces content-aware questions. (D) All existing frontier + steering tests pass. (E) New tests for narrow_candidates (collapsed and healthy stores).\n\nFILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (FrontierKind, narrow_candidates, compute_steering_question)" :op :assert}
